      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the embers of my own heart. He is gone, and with him, the very sun has vanished from my sky. I find myself staring into the darkness, wondering why I should bother to endure another dawn when the world has proven itself so cruel and hollow. It would be so much quieter, wouldn't it? To simply cease... to let the night take what is left of me.",
